text: The koka noodle stall hygiene and attitude need to be improved. Ordered koka noodle found one stain of hair stuck inside the cooked minced meat. Owner reluctantly takes back the noodle with comments “noodle were served without hair.”  Repeated twice and shout back to kitchen using Thai language where I don’t know what’s she was commenting.
The drink stall selling coffee, egg and bread for $5.50 !!!  Despite the listed price showing lower … this cost more than porridge I got for $4.40

Baby friendly. Has alot of baby chair.
Has the best western food around, if you want some fried chicken
